blog.title: No, said Aziraphale, it's ineffable.
blog.description:
Hello, I'm tinsnip.

Feeling rather ineffable these days. Expect a great deal of Good Omens.

Other interests: Star Trek. (Primarily DS9 and Cardassians.)
Pratchett. Wodehouse.
Cats. The Doctors Whom. Science. Cute things. Life truths. Pixels. And spiders, sometimes, so keep that in mind.

I post fic on AO3. It's quite good - you should have a look.

My work with Vyc on a Kardasi conlang is here.

Cardassian meta is found mostly under cardassians or kardasi.

If you enjoy my fanfic, why not buy me a coffee?

blog.name: gothicmarquise
blog.title: ~Secret Splendour~
blog.description:
Mediocre Aesthete. Lavender Menace. 24. Belfast.

Gothy-type and spooky things of both the floaty and deathrocky kind; an almost equal amount of pastels; Takarazuka (Sagiri Seina, Ranju Tomu, Asakaze Rei, Ayakaze Sakina, Misono Sakura); Discworld; ballet; corsets and other such fashion; vintage ephemera; any and every Alice in Wonderland or Holmes adaptation (except Sherlock), and indeed a variety of historical gay dramas not limited to Jeeves & Wooster, Poirot, Star Trek and AYBS?; vampires, mermaids, dragons and other mythical creatures; Dita von Teese, Sue Perkins, Katie McGrath and David Tennant. Pretty things, mostly.

The gorgeous background is by Cryptovolans~
